# Issue Management Rules

## Issue Creation
- Use clear, descriptive titles
- Provide detailed description of the problem or feature
- Add relevant labels (bug, enhancement, documentation, etc.)
- Assign to appropriate team member if known
- Include steps to reproduce for bugs

## Issue Comments
- Keep discussions focused and relevant
- Provide updates on progress
- Use @mentions to notify specific people
- Include code snippets or screenshots when helpful
- Be respectful and professional

## Closing Issues
- Verify the issue is fully resolved
- Reference the closing PR using `Closes #issue-number`
- Add a final comment summarizing the resolution
- Ensure proper labels are applied
- Only close when all acceptance criteria are met
